-- China's Stocks Decline for First Time in Six Days on Bank Lending Risks
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-26T03:38:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/china-s-stocks-decline-for-first-time-in-six-days-on-bank-lending-risks.html

          
          
             China’s stocks dropped for the
first time in six days, led by lenders and developers, on
concern banks won’t recoup all their loans to local governments.  
 The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, lost 12.44, or 0.5 percent, to
2,559.59 at the 11:30 a.m. break after rising as much as 0.5
percent.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          July 26 (Bloomberg) -- Steve Bernstein, chief executive officer of Oppenheimer Investments Asia Ltd., talks with Bloomberg's Haslinda Amin about his investment strategy for Asian stocks. 
     Bernstein, speaking in Hong Kong, also discusses the outlook for Chinese banks and initial public offerings. (Excerpt. Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
